<h2>JSON Request/Response Formats</h2>

<h3>Generate Request</h3>

<pre>
{
  "model": "llama2",
  "prompt": "Explain quantum computing",
  "system_prompt": "You are a physics expert",
  "format": "markdown",
  "temperature": 0.7,
  "top_k": 40,
  "top_p": 0.9
}
</pre>

<h3>Generate Response</h3>

<pre>
{
  "response": "Generated text from model...",
  "model": "llama2",
  "created_at": "2026-01-05T22:00:00Z",
  "done": true,
  "context": [array of context tokens],
  "total_duration": 1234567890,
  "load_duration": 123456789,
  "prompt_eval_count": 45,
  "prompt_eval_duration": 123456789,
  "eval_count": 100,
  "eval_duration": 987654321
}
</pre>

<h3>Chat Request</h3>

<pre>
{
  "conversation_id": "unique-id",
  "message": "Hello, how are you?",
  "model": "llama2",
  "system_prompt": "Be helpful and friendly"
}
</pre>

<h3>Chat Response</h3>

<pre>
{
  "conversation_id": "unique-id",
  "message": "Generated response...",
  "model": "llama2",
  "timestamp": "2026-01-05T22:00:00Z",
  "complete": true,
  "message_count": 5
}
</pre>

<h2>Database Integration</h2>

<h3>Conversation Storage</h3>

<p>Conversations are persisted in the Comserv database using DBIx::Class models:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Table:</strong> Conversations</li>
<li><strong>Fields:</strong> conversation_id (PK), user_id, model, created_at, updated_at</li>
<li>One conversation contains many messages</li>
<li>Messages include: message_id, conversation_id, role (user/assistant), content, timestamp</li>
</ul>

<h2>Error Handling</h2>

<p>Error handling uses Try::Tiny exception handling:</p>

<ul>
<li>JSON endpoints return error responses with HTTP 400/500 status codes</li>
<li>Web endpoints flash error messages and redirect</li>
<li>All errors logged with full context (file, line, user)</li>
<li>Validation errors include helpful user messages</li>
<li>Ollama connection failures handled gracefully with retry logic</li>
</ul>

<h2>Logging &amp; Monitoring</h2>

<p>All actions logged via Comserv::Util::Logging with:</p>

<ul>
<li>Timestamp</li>
<li>Username (or guest ID)</li>
<li>Action method name</li>
<li>Source file and line number</li>
<li>Log level (debug, info, warn, error)</li>
<li>Additional context (query parameters, response status)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Logging instance:</strong> `$self->logging` (lazy-loaded attribute)</p>

<h2>Dependencies &amp; Utilities</h2>

<h3>Perl Modules Used</h3>

<ul>
<li><strong>Moose</strong> - Object system with attributes</li>
<li><strong>namespace::autoclean</strong> - Namespace cleanup</li>
<li><strong>Try::Tiny</strong> - Exception handling</li>
<li><strong>JSON</strong> - JSON parsing and serialization</li>
<li><strong>Comserv::Util::Logging</strong> - Centralized logging</li>
<li><strong>Comserv::Model::Ollama</strong> - Ollama model interaction</li>
<li><strong>Data::UUID</strong> - UUID generation for guest sessions</li>
</ul>

<h3>External Services</h3>

<ul>
<li><strong>Ollama Server:</strong> External LLM server (configurable host/port)</li>
<li><strong>Ollama Registry:</strong> Model catalog for pulling models</li>
<li><strong>Database:</strong> Conversation persistence via DBIx::Class</li>
</ul>

<h2>Configuration</h2>

<p>Configuration stored in config file and environment variables:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>OLLAMA_HOST:</strong> Server hostname (default: localhost)</li>
<li><strong>OLLAMA_PORT:</strong> Server port (default: 11434)</li>
<li><strong>OLLAMA_API_BASE:</strong> API endpoint path</li>
<li><strong>OLLAMA_MODELS_DIR:</strong> Local model cache directory</li>
</ul>

<h2>Best Practices for Integration</h2>

<ul>
<li>Always validate model names against available models before querying</li>
<li>Handle Ollama connection timeouts gracefully (server may be starting)</li>
<li>Stream responses for long-running queries to provide user feedback</li>
<li>Preserve conversation context across multiple API calls</li>
<li>Log all user queries for audit and debugging purposes</li>
<li>Rate limit model pulls to prevent resource exhaustion</li>
<li>Validate JSON input thoroughly before passing to Ollama</li>
</ul>

<h2>Known Issues &amp; Workarounds</h2>

<h3>Database Blocker Issue (Known)</h3>

<p>Long multi-turn conversations may experience database persistence issues due to concurrent access patterns. Workaround: Reset conversation occasionally or use smaller context windows.</p>

<h3>GPU Memory Management</h3>

<p>Switching between large models requires manual memory clearing. Check server status before pulling very large models.</p>

<h2>Integration Points</h2>

<ul>
<li><strong>Ollama Model:</strong> Comserv::Model::Ollama handles Ollama communication</li>
<li><strong>Logging System:</strong> All actions logged via Logging utility</li>
<li><strong>Authentication:</strong> User session management and guest sessions</li>
<li><strong>Database:</strong> Conversation persistence and message history</li>
<li><strong>Configuration:</strong> External Ollama server connection settings</li>
</ul>

